inn1.comm: good length ball on off stump, Uthappa stands tall on the back foot and defends on the off side
fullish ball drifting on to the pads, Uthappa moves across and turns it off his pads for two to fine leg
excellent ball, pitches on a good length on off stump, Uthappa looks to close the face and turn in to the leg side, the ball seams away from him off the pitch and beats the outside edge
full ball outside off stump, Uthappa chases it and gets a thick edge wide of the two slips that are in place, the ball runs fine down to the third man fence, it's a very quick outfield this
good length ball on off stump, Uthappa gets forward defends with bat and pad close together
tight line and length from Taylor, Uthappa defends on the back foot
good pace and bolunce outside the off stump, Gambhir goes fishing with a wide swish and catches nothing
excellent length just outside the left-hander's off stump, Gambhir lets it go through to Ramdin
full ball straying down leg side, that's the first extra of the innings
good length ball pitching on leg and middle, Gambhir waits for it on the back foot and defends
a touch fuller in length, angling across the left-hander, Gambhir presses fprward and defends to cover
pitching just outside off stump and moves away from Gambhir who shoulders arms

that's the end of Gambhir! That was short and wide outside the off stump, Gambhir goes hard after it and slashes, he gets a very thick outside edge that flies straight to Lendl Simmons at third man who didn't have to move to take that catch
defended on the leg side
width offered outside the off stump and Uthappa punches superbly through covers to collect a boundary
and again, this time off the back foot, Uthappa didnt time this as well but he'll get two runs to deep cover
the timing is perfect this time! He punches sweetly on the front foot back past the bowler and the ball screams to the fence
defended on the front foot to square leg, Rania takes off for the single from the non-strikers end but Uthappa says no, Raina would have been out had there been a direct hit
that bounced a bit more off a good length, Uthappa gets behind the line and blocks
that was quick at 143kmh but the line was poor down leg side, Rania moves across and the ball hits the pad and runs down to the fence for leg byes
defended on the front foot on the off side
good length ball on off stump, Rania plays on the back foot and defends to point
pitches on middle stump and moves away from Rania who plays inside the line and the ball whizzes past the outside edge
pitches on a good length and bounces quite high, Rania lets it go
defended on the front foot back to the bowler
oh that was poor, poor line from Taylor who strayed down leg and the ball clipped Uthappa's pad, Ramdin should have collected that but he let it go through for four leg byes
outstanding shot, that was a length ball on middle and off stump, Uthappa pressed forward and punches firmly back past the bowler, four more
tight line and length outside off stump, Uthappa defends on the offside
strays on to the pads again, Uthappa leans across his stumps, uses his wrists to pick it up from middle and off and flick it prefectly through midwicket for four more
Taylor retorts with the bouncer, Uthappa went on the front foot and tried to hook, he wwas beaten comprehensively
slower ball on middle and leg, Uthappa flicks it off his pads through midwicket again, 12 runs from the over
short of a length ball on middle and leg, Rania moves back and drops it short of  midwicket for a quick single
good length ball on off and middle stump, Uthappa gets behind the line and defends with a straight bat
good ball, pitches short of a length outside off stump, Uthappa tries to drive on the rise but the ball hits the outside edge down to third man
pitches on middle and angles away from Raina, he opens the face and guides it to point
too wide outside off stump, Raina stands tall on the back foot, gets on top of the bounce and cuts through point for four, India are motoring along nicely
short of a length ball on leg stump, Raina flicks off his hips but straight to square leg
excellent start, forces the bottom edge from Uthappa and the ball bounces over the stumps
defended back past the bowler on the front foot
flicked off the hips to midwicket
good length ball on off stump, driven into the covers on the front foot
pitches outside leg stump and carries on down leg side, wide called
dabbed in front of covers on the front foot, they scamper through for a sharp single
shot! Uthappa plants his front foot forward to a ball that's a fraction too short, he drives on the put and times it superbly to the long-off fence
pitches short and angles wide outside off stump, Raina slashes at it but gets beaten
short of  a length outside off stump, Raina stands tall on the back foot and punches hard off the back foot to cover
short of a length ball on middle and leg, Uthappa moves across his stumps and flicks uppishly through midwicket
take that! short in length and wide outside off stump, Uthappa moves forward and gives it a fearful thump through covers, that scorched the turf through to the fence, India race to fifty
outstanding! fuller ball on leg and middle, Uthappa drives firmly down the ground and there's no stopping that, he's timing it perfectly today
aand again, straighter this time, Uthappa moves forward and drives through the line, one the ball beats mid-on and mid-off it's four!
flicked off the pads to midwicket
Emrit strays down leg side again, Bowden says that's wide
good length and line on middle and off stump, Raina comes forward and plays it back to the bowler
pushed to mid-off for a quick single
good length again on off snd middle stump, Uthappa looks to come forward and plays to midwicket

massive massive hit! short and wide outside off stump, Uthappa gets on the front foot and blasts that over the wide long-on fence, that's his fifty off just 32 balls, he;'s making a strong claim for the World Cup!
drifts down leg side, Uthappa clips it off his pads down to fine leg
defended on the front foot back past the bowler
poor line, straying down leg side, Emrit is struggling with the left-right combination, Raina moves across and gets a bit of pad on it down to the fine-leg fence
fuller length on middle and leg, Uthappa moves across and clips it off his pads to short fine leg who is up in the circle
Bravo gets the same treatment as the others, too much width on offer outside the off stump, Uthappa gets forward and slams it through covers
and take that as well says Uthappa, that was aslower ball from Bravo, Uthappa once more gets on the front foot and hits through the line, it sails over the long-off fence
four more, he times the drive perfectly through covers again, Uthappa is on fire and the crowd are chanting his name!
short ball and Uthappa tries to hook, he gets a bit of bat on it and it clears the wicketkeeper for four more to fine leg
punched firmly down the ground and a mis-field at mid-on allows the single, Uthappa retains strike
good length ball on off stump, Uthappa gets forward and defends

Gayle breaks the partnership! That was bowled flat on off and middle, Uthappa looks to heave it down the ground, the ball takes the splice of the bat and goes high in the air to Simmons  who back-pedals at mid-off to take the catch, relief for West Indies
full ball on off stump, square driven to point
Gayle drops short and Raina is on the back foot in a flash, he punches through cover and places it perfectly, Dwayne Smith chases it but the outfield is too wuick
defended on the front foot to cover
pushed through quickly on off stump, Raina gets on the front foot and defends
fullish length on middle and leg stump, Tendulkar leans across and clips it to mid-on
short of a length ball on the thigh, Tendulkar moves across his stumps and flicks to Morton at square leg
fullish length on off stump, Tendulkar gets on the front foot and punches to cover, he gets the single and the crowd roar in approval
short of a length and too wide outside off stump, Raina drives on the risse but can't beat the infield at cover
driven firmly yet again but straight to the fielder at mid-off
short of a length on middle and off stump, Raina presses forward and punches to cover
short of a length ball on off stump, Tendulkar looks to drive on the back foot through cover but gets an inside edge behind square leg
forced through midwicket for a single
pushed off the back foot to mid-on
full ball on middle stump, Tendulkar flicks through midwicket to pick up another single
pushed flat through the air on off stump, Raina pushes softly to mid-off for a quick single
flicked off the legs to midwicket for a single to end the over
short of a length ball on middle and leg, Tendulkar clips it off his pads to midwicket
glorious shot! and trademark Tendulkar, that was short of a length outside off stump, Tendulkar moved forward and towards the ball and drove through covers for four
dabbed behind square on the off side for a single
Powell lets a bouncer rip, that is far too high and Raina swerves out of the way, the ball bounces over Ramdin's head for four wides
good length ball on off stump, Raina moves forward and plays it with an open face to point
flicked off the hips to midwicket
this is a perfect batting strip for Raina just planted his foot forward to one that was short of a length and drove through the line, he lofted that with ease over covers for four more
short ball drifting down leg side, Tendulkar flicks it through midwicket for a single
quick ball on middle and off stump, Raina waits for it on the back foot and defends to mid-off
defended to point on the front foot
fired down leg side, wide called
straighter line on middle and off, Raina covers the line and defends
pitches on leg stump and Raina flicks off his pads wide of the man at short fine leg
full ball on middle and leg stump, Tendulkar comes forward and flicks, Lara dives to his left at midwicket to save runs, West Indies have been sharp in the field in spite of the run-glut
and Raina gives him a warm welcome, a touch too full and Raina gets forward and lofts through the line high over mid-on, the ball bounces just inside the boundary and India get four more
short of a length ball angling into Raina from round the wicket, Raina plays back and defends towards point
good length ball outside off stump, Raina tries to drive through the line and doesn't control it, he hits it in the air to Lara, who takes a sharp catch at cover
poor ball, full and on leg stump, Dravid leans across and flicks but Morton dives to his left to pull off an excellent save
short of a length outside off stump, Dravid plays it on the back foot and drives to mid-off
slower ball outside off stump, Dravid spots it and plays it late to point
short of a length on off and middle, Tendulkar pushes it wide of mid-on for a single
tossed up slowly on off and middle but the length is too full, Dravid comes forward and plays the on-drive to perfection, he places it between short midwicket and mid-on and gets four
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
short ball outside off stump, Dravid rocks back and cuts past point for four more
drifting on to the pads, Dravid forces it through midwicket
a touch too short again on middle and leg, Tendulkar pushes it to mid-on for a single
full toss on leg stump, Tendulkar will feel that he missed out on easy runs, he tried to flick it but didn't make contact
full again on leg stump, this time Tendulkar times the flick well but hits it straight to Morton at square leg
full length again on middle and leg, Tendulkar punches firmly to mid-on
short of a length outside off stump, Tendulkar steers it to third man and they run a quick two runs
simply superb, Taylor bowls it just short of a length and Tendulkar gets forward and punches the on-drive back past the bowler, no stopping that
flicked off the hips to midwicket
short of a length outside off stump, Dravid stands tall on the back foot and plays it to point
short of a length again angling into Dravid's pads, he flicks it and times it well but can't beat midwicket
slower ball on off and middle, Dravid defends on the front foot
good length ball outside off stump, Dravid moves on the back foot and plays it towards cover point
short of a length outside off stump, Dravid gets back and punches firmly to cover, he doesn't find the gap  in the infield
poor bowling, short and wide outside off stump, a gift really and Dravid says thank you by flaying it through cover-point for four
drifting on to the pads, that's too easy for Tendulkar who closes the face to work it through square leg for two more
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
straying on to the pads again, Taylor's lucky to escape punsihment there as the ball hist Tendulkar's pads
full on the pads again, Tendulkar flicks easily to deep midwicket to bring up India's 150
punched to cover on the front foot
slower ball on off and middle, Tendulkar plays back and defends back to the bowler
short and wide outside off stump, Dravid jumps up on the back foot and cuts hard, he doesn't beat the fielder at point
short of a length outside off stump, Dravid punches off the back foot through cover for a single
slower ball but it's mis-directed down leg side, another wide
short and wide outside off stump, Tendulkar reaches out for it and hits it to deep cover for  one
better line and length, much closer to off stump, Dravid plays it with soft hands in front of point and gets a quick single
fullish length drifting on to middle and leg, Tendulkar turns it off his pads to deep midwicket
again Dravid uses soft hands to drop it in front of point and steal a sharp single
what a shot! That was pitched just short of  a length close to off stump, Dravid jumps up on the back foot and hits it hard into the ground, the ball bounces over point and races to the fence
defended on the back foot to midwicket
slower ball on middle and leg stump, Dravid moved across too early and the ball hits the pad and trickles to midwicket
defended to point on the back foot
short of a length outside off stump, Dravid tries to force it off the back foot through covers but doesn't time it well
worked off the pads to deep midwicket for a single
good length ball just outside off stump, Dravid gets forward and steers it to point
dropped short on the off side, Dravid looks to steal the single again but Tendulkar sends him back
slower ball but it is too full on leg stump, Dravid waits for it and flicks in front of square for four more, Emrit will learn that he can't bowl there to him
drifting on to the pads again, Dravid flicks to deep square leg for a single
and again he drifts on to the pads, Tendulkar clips it in front of midwicket for two more
tight line and length to finish the over, Tendulkar plays it back to the bowler
driven down to long-on for an easy single
tossed up and turning in, Tendulkar gets forward and drives it down to long-on for yet another easy singe, that's all the have to do to maintain a healthy run rate
again punched off the back-foot to the long-on region. Lara will have to cut off these single and make the batsmen go for big shot to rope in a wicket, at the moment it's looking all too easy

oh dear! turned away towards square leg and they scamper through for a single, Mroton's throw at the bowler's end fails to hit the target, there is no one backing up and the ball races away to the fence. Horrible cricket from the visitors
flighted delivery, worked away through midwicket and a single is added to the total
punched straight to the fielder at short midwicket
worked away through midwicket
punched off the back-foot to the short midwicket region, just enough room and they scamper through for a single
again tucked away throgh midwicket
slightly short and pulled away through midwicket
and again, worked away towards his favourtie midwicket region
comes down and misses the target, stumping changes goes begging
defended on the front-foot
looks to run it down to third man but fails to make contact
and the usual, clipped away through midwicket for a single
nudged away behind square leg for a single
punched off the back-foot to long-on
bit of width offered and Tendulkar cuts it away through point
turned away with the spin to deep square leg
punched off the back-foot to the long-on region, it's raining singles here
and once again they pinch a single to long-on
worked away off the pads to square leg
fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
punched off the back-foot ande Dravid finds the gap between the cover fielders
cut away off the back-foot to deep backward point
better line and length, defended watchflly
comes down the track and drives it down to long-on for a single, Is Lara watching?
defended back to the bowler
goes for the reverse sweep but fails to make contact
off the pads to the short fine leg region
clipped away off the pads to deep square leg, West Indies continues to bleed runs
tossed up and turning in, Tendulkar comes forward and works it away through midwicket
runs it off the back-foot to the gully region and the single brings up India's 200
forced away towards point
worked away on the leg side and the party continues
punched down to long-on
played away towards gully and finally they succede in cutting off a single
worked away sqare on the leg side, and the usual single is added to the total
easily driven down to long-on, you guessed it
worked away behind square leg
driven away towards cover, just wide of the fielder there, Tendulkar calls for the single but Dravid is not interested
worked away straight to the fielder at square leg
fullish ball on off stump, driven down the ground to long-off for one
flicked off the pads to Morton at square leg
short ball on middle and leg, Tendulkar pulls it to deep square leg
cut away off the back foot to deep point
driven through midwicket for another single
touch short outside off stump, Dravid plays the reverse-sweep and uses Gayle's pace to play it fine to the third man fence
short and wide outside off, Tendulkar cuts it to third man to move on to 49
that's his fifty, Chennai gives him a huge cheer as he flicks it off his pads to deep midwicket to collect the single, well-played Sachin
Dravid now reaches his fifty with a drive down the ground, huge cheers go round the ground again
cut off the back foot to deep point
worked off the pads towards sqaure leg
full ball driven down the ground for one
Gayle drops it short and Dravid goes on the back foot and pulls to deep midwicket
dropped! A tough catch does down, Tendulkar chipped that in the air to midwicket where Lara jumps up with one hand but doesn't hold on to the catch
dabbed short on the off side for a sharp single
another quick single taken, this time Dravid steers it to point
cut to deep point on the back foot to bring up the 100 partnership
worked off the pads through square leg for one
driven to mid-on on the front foot
short ball just outsude the off stump, Dravid goes back and tries to cut but the extra bounce beats the outside edge
punched off the back foot to point
short of  a  length ball outside off stump, steered down to third man for a single
drifts on to the pads this time and Tendulkar steers it off his pads behind square, he runs the first run quickly but still can't manage the second
played into the covers for a single to end the over
drifting on to leg once again, Dravid turns it off his pads for a single to fine leg
short ball outside off stump, Tendulkar backs away and tries to cut but gets beaten
played to deep midwicket for a single
caught on the fence! Dravid goes after Gayle and slogs it from off stump down to long-on, he doesn't get enough on it to clear the fence and Emrit takes a well-judged catch inches inside the fence
bowled quickly through the air on off stump, defended back to the bowler
driven back to Gayle on the front foot, Gayle finishes a fine spell in which he's taken two crucial wickets
short of a length ball on off stump, steered down to third man for a single
that took off! Bravo pitched that just short of a length and it rose sharply on Yuvraj who dropped his wrists and swayed out of the way
short of a length ball on off stgump, Yuvraj plays back and drives to cover
pitches wide outside off stump and moves wider away, umpire Shastri says it's too wide
good length ball on off stump, Yuvraj stands in his crease and punches firmly to cover
good length again on off stump, Yuvraj doesn't move much in his crease, just stands his grounds and punches to mid-on
driven on the front foot to mid-on yet again, just two runs off that over, good stuff from Bravo
tossed up on leg stump, Tendulkar moves across, gets down on one knee and sweeps fine for a single
pushed down to long off for a single to get off the mark
bowled flat and fast on middle stump, Tendulkar plays back and defends to midwicket
the yorker bowled at serious pace for a spinner, Tendulkar manages to get his bat down in time
slower through the air on middle and leg, Tendulkar drives down to long on
defended to cover on the front foot

caught and what a catch! Fullish length on off and middle stump, Tendulkar tries to force it over mid-on but doesn't time it well, Morton moves to his left at mid-on and takes a splendid catch, moving backwards over his shoulder
defended to point on the front foot
good length ball on off stump, Karthik gets behind the line and defends to cover
slower ball on off and middle stump, defended back to the bowler
fullish ball on off stump, Karthik gets forward and pushes it through covers for a single
wide ball outside off stump, Yuvraj chases it and gets betaen
defended on the front foot behin square on the off side
worked through midwicket for a single
Samuels drops it short on middle and Yuvraj goes back and punches down the ground for one
Karthik drives down to long on for another single
defended to point on the front foot
good length ball outside off stump, Karthik gets forward and drives through cover point for one
Bravo bounces Yuvraj again who tries to pull, he ends up playing a very awkward shot, and gets a thick edge down to fine leg, Emrit runs across and fields superbly
pushed to midwicket for another single
punched firmly on the front foot for one more, that's four singles in four balls
a touch too full and Karthik plants the front foot forward and drives through cover for one
full ball on the pads, Yuvraj clips it through wide mid-on for one more to end the over
driven hard into the cover region for a single
fired quick down leg side, Yuvraj tries to flick but gets beaten, wide called
full ball outside off stump, Yuvraj tries to drive hard through cover but misses, Ramdin misses the take and the ball lobs  off his gloves to short third man
cut to deep point for one
full ball on off stump, Karthik heaves it in the air to Gayle at deep midwicket, it's a dolly of a catch but Gayle drops it, that was a sitter and Gayle himself can't believe it
defended on the off side
full ball on the pads, Yuvraj clips it off his toes behind square leg for four runs, superb timing
good length ball on off stump, that bounces a bit more than usual, Karthik tries to drive down the ground but gets beaten by the bounce
good length and line on off stump, Karthik gets forward and defends solidly
short of a length ball angling into middle and leg, Karthik works it off his hips for one
caught and bowled, Bravo gave him another short one and Yuvraj tries to pull that from just outside off, he hits it high on the bat and skies it, Bravo calls for the catch and judges it well
left alone outside the off stump
Karthik goes! West Indies are back with a bang, Bravo bowls it in the channel outside off stump, Karthik fends at it and gets a faint nick through to Ramdin
defended back to the bowler
pushed quickly through the air, defended on the front foot
defended to the leg side
defended to midwicket on the front foot
steered to point on the front foot
played with an open face wide off the fielder at short third man
short of a length ball outside off stump, Agarkar opens the face and runs it down to third man
Bravo bounces Powar who moves out of the way of that one, is Bravo setting him up for the yorker?
good length ball on off stump, Powar plays back and pokes at it, the ball beats the outside edge
short of a length ball on off stump, defended to point on the back foot
short of a length again on off stump, Powar hardly moves as he defends that to cover, the crowd is getting restless
Bravo drifts on to the pads and Powar clips it down to deep backward square leg for a single
driven to long-on for a single
driven back to the bowler
defended back to Samuels on the front foot

Samuels drops it a touch short just outside off stump but bowls it quicker, Agarkar tries to steer it down to third man but gets a thick edge, Morton moves quickly to his left at short third man and dives low to his left to take a sharp catch
fired down leg side, wide called
defended to point on the front foot
worked off the pads to midwicket, Samuels completes a superb spell

short of a length on off stump, Powar guides it to point, Kumble calls him through for a single, Powar is really struggling to make his ground at the non-striker's end, had Samuels hit, India would have been nine down
short and wide outside the off stump, steered down to third man
excellent line and length just outside off stump, Powar plays forward and efends but gets beaten
short and wide outside off stump, Powar frees his arms and gives it a mighty thump, he gets a single to deep point for his effort
tight line and length on off stump, not giving the batsman any room this time, defended on the front foot
good length ball angling into off and middle, Kumble plays forward with bat close to pad and defends
short and wide outside off stump, Powar backs away and smacks it, Lara dives to his right and make sa superb save
full ball drifting into the pads, searching for the yorker was Taylor, Powar flicks to deep midwicket
pushed to deep point on the back foot for one
Taylor tests Powar with a bouncer, that's the one bouncer for the over

soft dismissal, Taylor fires in the fuller ball, Powar doesn't move his feet an inch and tries to close the face of the bat to play it through midwicket, he gets an inside edge on to pad after which the ball balloons up to Taylor who takes the easiest of catches
fullish ball angled into the pads, Sreesanth moves across and tries to flick, he gets a single to square leg
Bravo tests Sreesanth with the bouncer this time, he ducks straight into it and gets hit on the helmet
another superb short ball, rears up at Sreesanth who moves his head out of the way and smells the ball as it goes past
pushed into the covers for a single
full ball outside off stump, Kumble tries to smash it through covers but doesn't time it well
short of a length ball on the hips, Kumble turns it in front of midwicket for one
that's the end of that, Bravo bangs in another short ball and Sreesanth doesn't know what to do, he fends at it awkwardly, the ball hits the glove and lobs to Morton at slip

inn2.comm: Agarkar strikes first ball, an identical dismissal to the Cuttack game, a virtual replay really, Agarkar pitches that ball around the off stump, it straightens back into Gayle who hardly moves hiw feet, the ball thuds into the pad first before hitting the bat and Billy Bowden says that's out, he's got it right too

Agarkar fires in the yorker, Morton digs it out to cover, uthappa picks up the balla nd under-arms it back towards the stumps, Morton had turned his back to the ball and got hit on the back of the neck, he's in a lot of pain out there
good length ball on off stump, Morton chops it down on the off side towards uthappa at cover, Uthappa picks up and fires at the non-strikers end, Morton covers his head and completes the single
sprayed wide outside the off stump, wide called
good length ball pitching on off and middle and bending back into the left-hander, Smith tucks it off his pads for a single to square leg
pitches on a good length outside off stump and seams away from the right-hander, Morton gets forward, begins to play at it but lets it go in the end
another very wide ball outside off stump, Bowden says thats another wide
bowled on a good length outside off stump,Morton lets it go through to Karthik
short and wide outside the off stump, a real loosner from Sreesanth, Smith rocks back and cuts hard through point for four
oh that's terrible from Sreesanth, the seam's perfectly upright as usual but it's very wide outside off stump  and it's too wide for Karthik to collect it, five wides down to the third man fence
what's going on here, this one's sprayed down leg side, and so wide that Karthik didn't even attempt to collect that, five more wides, 14 runs off one ball so far
good length ball on off stump, he bowled that with a scrambled seam, defended on the back foot on the off side
fullish length with a lot of swing back into the left hander, Smith was beaten by the swing and got hit on the pad
good length loutside the off stump, that swung back into the left-hander as well, Smith watched it closely and let it go
superb placement, that was a rather good ball but Smith gets forward and punches between cover and mid-off, he picks the gap and times it sweetly enough to reach the fence
that's a rank half-volley and Smith thumps it thorugh cover for four more, Sreesanth finishes a nightmare over
good length ball on off stump, Morton opens the face and guides it wide of yuvraj at point who moves to his left and makes the save
good length ball on off stump, Morton gets behind the line and defends
excellent ball in the channel outside off stump, Morton feels for it without moving his feet, the ball swings away from him and beats the edge
that flew from short of a length and bounced high over Morton, Karthik takes it over his head,  Bowden calls it wide
Agarkar has another! Poor shot from Morton who fished at a wide one that was swinging away from him, his feet stayed rooted to the spot and he feathered a nick through to Karthik
Agarkar bowls it wide outside off stump, Samuels lets it go
good length ball on off stump, Samuels plays it to point where Yuvraj does the fielding, he's looking a little ginger in the field
pitches on middle and leg stump on a good length, that swings back into Smith who plays back and gets hit on the pad
outstanding save, Sreesanth bowled it short and wide outside off stump, Yuvraj dived full length to his left to stop a scorching cut shot, no sign of gingerness that time
full ball on off stump, squeezed out to point
great length from Sreesanth and a tight line too, pinning Samuels on the back foot, he defends that back down the pitch, Sreesanth sprints up and does the fielding
strays in line this time and sends it down leg side, Samuels runs it down to fine leg
full ball on off and middle stump, Smith digs it out to mid-off, good comeback from Sreesanth, just two runs off this over
banged in short and wide outside off stump, Samuels lets it go and Bowden calls it wide
beaten by one that pitched outside off stump and moved a shade away, Samuels fends at it but gets beaten
this is poor, another wide ball outside off stump
good length ball on off stump, Samuels plays back and defends on the off side, Yuvraj races in from point and prevents any thought of a single
good short ball and well played, that rose from just short of  a length, it got up to neck height, Samuels took his bottom hand off the bat and kept it down
